    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The primary hemolysis acceptability claim (see bindsClaim) is supported by an extensive prose narrative citing the FDA interlaboratory PIV study, the Taskin four-pump hemolysis validation dataset, Monte Carlo UQ results, and a three-level mesh refinement study. On the basis of this narrative the assessment team judges the claim credible and accepts the package. All 13 credibility factors have been reviewed; 7 were formally assessed and 6 were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite the gaps, the convergent evidence described in the claim description is considered sufficient for the Low assurance level target. Decision: Accepted.",
